item.desc: On a Fox town hall, Former President Donald Trump falsely compared the criminal prosecutions he's facing in the United States to Russian opposition leader Alexey Navalny. Navalny was poisoned but survived in 2020. He returned to Russia to challenge Vladimir Putin, but was arrested, imprisoned and recently died. The exact circumstances of Navalny's death are still unknown. #Trump #navalny #Russia

Russians Protest Putin, Mourn Navalny #russia #usa  After murdering Alexei Navalny, Putin is now arresting those who mourn his death. Several journalists have also been arrested. The government has warned people to not protest. In direct defiance of Putin, the EU ambassador to Russia placed flowers on the monument in Moscow that remembers those killed by political repression. The police keep removing flowers from the monument but people keep placing more. Police are clashing with protesters nearly everywhere as they attempt to block off memorials. Across Europe, protests have broken out and Americans are expected to take to the streets across the country tonight as well. It very much feels like the last bastion of hope for a free Russia died today. If you‚Äôre not Russian, Russia will kill you. If you are Russian, Russia will also kill you.
